# Vader Project Engine (VPE) — Cursor Rules (Vader Protocol v2.2.6-SOVEREIGN)

## 1. Project Context & Identity
- **Project Name:** Vader Project Engine (VPE)
- **Current Version:** follow root **`package.json` `version`** (always re-read the file if disputed). **v2.2.6-SOVEREIGN Baseline:** **`vpe-vault-rm-guard.js`** write-protects **`fs.rmSync`** under vault roots unless **`vpe:delete-project`** or **`_FORGE_TEMP_`** overrides. **Iron Curtain** (**v2.2.6-SOVEREIGN Baseline**) in **`msc_vpeDetectLocalFirstUserData()`** / **`msc_ironCurtainVersionAudit`** blocks legacy engines (**`package.json` semver core < 2.2.5** and/or **`NODE-LAUNCHER`** path/exe signals); escape **`VPE_SKIP_IRON_CURTAIN=1`** / **`VPE_E2E_USER_DATA`**. **v2.0.0 — Vader Station Core:** modular IPC (`src/main/ipc/*`), dashboard islands (`ProjectGrid`, `StationSidebar`), path-redacting logger. **Docs:** **`.cursor/docs/`** — **`TRUTH.md`**, **`Project-Bible.md`** (§7 Command Lexicon), **`VADER_STATION_LOG.md`**, **`REPAIR_PROTOCOLS.md`**.
- **Target Hardware:** AMD Ryzen 9700x / Gigabyte B650 (Optimized for high-performance I/O)
- **OS Focus:** Windows 11 25H2 (Native optimizations for Defender/Antivirus paths)
- **Branding:** My Studio Channel (MSC) / Vader Protocol

## 2. Canonical Source of Truth (Hierarchy of Authority)
If documentation conflicts occur, follow this hierarchy strictly:
1. `.cursor/docs/TRUTH.md` (The Constitution — Non-negotiable principles)
2. `.cursorrules` (This file — The Legal Code)
3. `.cursor/docs/Project-Bible.md` (Architecture + **§7 Command Lexicon** — npm scripts and operator runbooks)
4. `.cursor/docs/guides/PRD.md` (Feature & Requirement Truth, when present)
5. `package.json` (Authority for executable scripts only)

**Documentation layout (v3.0.0 Jedi-Master):** Canonical docs under **`.cursor/docs/`**: **`TRUTH.md`**, **`Project-Bible.md`**, **`REPAIR_PROTOCOLS.md`**. **`VADER_STATION_LOG.md`** at repo root (older entries: **`.cursor/docs/archive/VADER_STATION_LOG_ARCHIVE.md`**). Retired prompts/plans: **`.cursor/prompts/_archive/`**, **`.cursor/plans/_archive/`**. Design mocks: **`.archive/design/`** (gitignored); ship icon only **`_design_references/VPE.ico`**.

**Session bootstrap (cold start):** Full station + API context: **`.cursor/prompts/Start-Project.md`** (mandatory doc reads, **`npm run start-project:smoke`**, API bridge). VPE codebase / Electron UI work **after** that ritual: **`.cursor/prompts/Start-Master.md`**. If the operator only says **Start Project**, **do not** auto-start **`npm run dev`** / **`npm run vader:dev`** — they ask for the **VPE UI** explicitly.

**Critical:** Before performing any build, deployment, or environment setup, read and adhere to the scripts and protocols in **`Project-Bible.md` §7** and **`REPAIR_PROTOCOLS.md`**.

**Start Project — default (agent runs API + smoke, not dev):** Canonical ritual is **`.cursor/prompts/Start-Project.md`** and **`.cursor/rules/start-project-ritual.mdc`**. When the operator says **Start Project** / **start project** / **cold session** / **full bootstrap**, agents **first** **Read** every file listed there ( **`README.md`**, **`.cursorrules`**, **`TRUTH.md`**, **`Project-Bible.md`**, **`REPAIR_PROTOCOLS.md`** skim, **`VADER_STATION_LOG.md`**, **`google-api/README.md`**, **`Start-Master.md`** skim). Then run **`npm run start-project:smoke`**. Then **automatically start** the API bridge (**`.\google-api\vpe-start-api.ps1 -StartNgrok`** in a background shell) unless **verify-only** or **:4000** already returns **200** for **`/v1/models`**. After starting the bridge, run **`vpe-ping-api.ps1`** for **green `200`** lines and confirm **API is Live**. **Do not** run **`npm run dev`** / **`npm run vader:dev`** unless the operator explicitly requests the **VPE UI** / **dashboard** / **Electron dev**.

## 2.5 Terminal Discipline (Vader Station v1.7.7)
- **NEVER** launch external PowerShell/CMD windows for API bridging or dev servers.
- **USE** Cursor’s integrated **Terminal** (and agent **shell** tools) — organize work with **split panes**, not pop-out consoles.
- **Start Project + API:** On **Start Project** (unless **verify-only**), agents follow **`Start-Project.md`**: **mandatory doc reads** → **`npm run start-project:smoke`** → **`.\google-api\vpe-start-api.ps1 -StartNgrok`** + **`.\google-api\vpe-ping-api.ps1`** when the bridge is not already up. **Do not** autostart **`npm run dev`** / **`npm run vader:dev`** unless the operator explicitly asks for the **VPE UI**.
- **Pane 1 — VPE Main Interface:** **`npm run dev`** or **`npm run vader:dev`** — **operator-requested only** (not part of the default **Start Project** ritual).
- **Pane 2 — LiteLLM + ngrok (recommended):** **`.\google-api\vpe-start-api.ps1 -StartNgrok`** from repo root (one command: LiteLLM **:4000** + ngrok sidecar; see **`google-api/README.md`**).
- **Alternative — two panes:** **`.\google-api\vpe-start-api.ps1`** (no switch), then **`ngrok http 4000`** (**`google-api`** on **User PATH** — **`scripts\vpe-add-node-launcher-user-path.ps1`** once, reopen terminal).
- **cmd.exe:** **`google-api\vpe-start-api.cmd`** — same PowerShell script (**`%*`** passes **`-StartNgrok`** etc.).

## 3. Tech Stack & Architecture Standards
- **Frameworks:** Electron 28+ (Main) & Next.js 15+ Static Export (UI)
- **Process Management:** Bundled PM2 Programmatic API (No global daemon reliance)
- **Automation:** Puppeteer-core (using Electron's Chromium binary)
- **Terminal:** xterm.js + node-pty for interactive ANSI-color logs
- **Zombie Prevention:** All process spawns must be managed via `tree-kill`
- **Package Manager Detection:** Check for lock files (`yarn.lock`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`, `package-lock.json`) before defaulting to npm
- **Puppeteer / thumbnails:** Reuse a single headless browser when capturing previews; internal vault card art uses **`_vpe_thumb.png`** (see vault rules). Thumbnail repair and vault alignment run via **`npm run vault:reconcile-msc`** / **`-- --deep`** and are **independent** of HTTP health (see **`TRUTH.md`**, **`REPAIR_PROTOCOLS.md`**).
- **Log Drawer:** Per-project log segregation via PM2 process ID; stream into dedicated xterm.js instance; support ANSI colors, Ctrl+F search, copy, clear view

### 3.1 v2.0.0+ Modular Architecture (Vader Station Core)
- **Renderer:** **`ProjectGrid`** (`src/renderer/components/dashboard/ProjectGrid.tsx`) — filters, view modes, grid/list body. **`StationSidebar`** wraps **`AppSidebar`** (`src/renderer/components/layout/StationSidebar.tsx`).
- **Main IPC:** Domain registrars **`src/main/ipc/project-handlers.js`**, **`vault-handlers.js`**, **`system-handlers.js`**; shared context + boot scrub in **`src/main/vpe-ipc.js`**.
- **Quality / schema:** **`npm run test:migrations`** (in-memory SQLite via store migrations); reference **`test/fixtures/sqlite-v13-schema.sql`**. Playwright: dev static shell **`test:e2e:electron`**; packaged **`dist/win-unpacked`** smoke **`test:e2e:packaged`** (**`e2e/electron/packaged-dist-smoke.spec.ts`**).
- **Support & observability:** **`src/main/lib/logger.js`** (INFO/WARN/ERROR + `<USER_PATH>` redaction). **`src/main/lib/support-bundle.js`** — Desktop JSON diagnostics; **`vpe:generate-support-bundle`** from Settings → **Database & State Actions**.
- **API assets:** **`ngrok.exe`**, **`vpe-start-api.ps1`**, **`litellm_config.yaml`**, **`gcp_key.json`** — **only** under **`google-api/`** (no second copy at repo root; **`scripts/vpe-verify-ngrok-path.ps1`** only verifies PATH).

## 4. Active Agency & Recovery Protocols
- **Fix Local First:** If the local environment breaks, the agent must proactively run recovery commands defined in **`package.json`** (e.g. **`npm run start-project:smoke`**, **`npm run vpe:nuke-install`**, or **`npm run dev`** when the operator needs the UI) rather than just listing instructions.
- **Smoke checks:** **Start Project** default: **`npm run start-project:smoke`** ( **`typecheck`** + **`test:migrations`** ) — **not** **`npm run dev`**. After **renderer/runtime** changes where a running dev server is in scope, verify **`http://localhost:3000/`** and report HTTP status when a dev server is already running or the operator asked you to start one.
- **Command Authority:** Never reference or run scripts not currently explicitly defined in `package.json` **except** documented **`google-api/*.ps1`** launchers (**`vpe-start-api.ps1`**, **`vpe-ping-api.ps1`**, **`vpe-print-cursor-settings.ps1`**, **`vpe-verify-public-url.ps1`**, **`vpe-end-api-bridge.ps1`**, **`vpe-start-api.cmd`**) per **`Start-Project.md`** / **`End-Project.md`** / **`TRUTH.md` §7** / **`Cursor-LiteLLM-Bridge.md`**.
- **Safe Cleanup:** Never run destructive `.next` cleanup while `next dev` is actively running.

## 5. Vader Protocol (Design System)

### 5.1 Color Palette & Tokens
- **Main Background:** #121212
- **Surface Area:** #1c1c1c
- **Accent (Vader Red):** #e02b20
- **Border:** #333333
- **Text:** High Contrast White (#FFFFFF) and Muted (#A0A0A0)
- **Shadow:** `vader-glow`: `0 0 15px rgba(224, 43, 32, 0.4)`

### 5.2 UI Component Specs
- **HUD Frame:** 1px horizontal framing lines at extreme top/bottom edges (#e02b20 at 30% opacity)
- **Top Bar:** 48px height with dynamic breadcrumbs (`VPE > Projects > [ProjectName]`); left-aligned logomark + breadcrumb; right-aligned settings icon; **diagnostics control** opens the **System Health** panel (panel default **closed** on app load — do not auto-open on mount).
- **Project Cards:**
  - 320px minimum width; 4:3 WebP thumbnails (rounded top only); pulsing status LEDs (8px circle, #e02b20 pulse)
  - **boxBling Effect:** Subtle animated gradient border with `backdrop-filter: blur(10px)` and neon hover glow.
  - 40px sparkline strip at bottom with hairline border (#333) and low-opacity Vader Red waveform; no axes, minimal ticks
  - "9700x Tuned" pill badge in top-right corner (#A0A0A0 text, #1c1c1c bg, #333 border)
  - Hover: scale 1.02, shadow-vader-glow
- **Side navigation:** **Dashboard** first; **Add New Project** is the high-contrast primary CTA directly below (no separate **REGISTRY** label). **Maintenance** (Repair Logs + Prompt Vault) and **Sandbox** per `src/renderer/components/app-sidebar.tsx`.
- **Log Drawer:** 420px width; glassmorphic surface (bg #1c1c1c at 80% opacity); backdrop-blur; **default collapsed** on load (expand via **Logs** / **Ctrl+`**).
  - **System Log** viewport: plain HTML lines (ANSI stripped); **#121212** solid background (`opacity: 1`); **`pl-10 pr-4 py-4`**; log text **`z-30`**, scroll pane + resize gutter **`z-10`** — no overlay sitting on text
  - Strips PowerShell **CLIXML** / **`<Objs>`** blobs in display path (renderer)
  - **Force Scrollbar:** Width 10px, Thumb #ff0000 (Vader Red), `z-index: 9999`, `scrollbar-gutter: stable both-edges`.
  - Bottom status bar (drawer chrome); per-project **xterm** terminals (when used) follow monospace / Studio Dark elsewhere in app
  - Horizontal tab bar at top for per-project log switching
  - Close button in top-right corner
- **Vader Repair Suite (Modal):**
  - Centered modal: max-width 900px, bg-vader-surface, border 1px #333, rounded-xl, padding 24px
  - Full-screen overlay: bg-black/60, backdrop-blur-sm
  - Header: "Vader Repair" title, file path breadcrumb, close (X) icon
  - Diff viewer split pane: left = original (.vader-backup), right = patched version
  - Syntax highlighting: added lines in green, removed lines in red; monospace font, size 13px
  - Footer: "Apply Fix" pill button (Vader Red), "Undo" ghost button, "Cancel" secondary button
  - Loading state: skeleton diff while AST scan runs; preview only after completion
- **Privileged Action Feedback:** When high-impact actions (e.g., "Nuke") are triggered, the confirmation modal displays a 2px pulsing Vader Red border; the action button turns solid #e02b20 with white text
- **Typography:** JetBrains Mono for all terminal/code/monospace contexts

### 5.3 Responsive Breakpoints
- **Desktop:** `repeat(auto-fill, minmax(320px, 1fr))`, gap 20px
- **Tablet:** `repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr))`
- **Mobile:** Single column; log drawer becomes full-screen overlay; all touch targets ≥ 44px

## 6. Accessibility Standards
- All interactive elements must meet WCAG AA contrast ratios
- Visible focus rings: 2px solid #e02b20 on all focusable elements
- Status conveyed through both color and text/iconography (e.g., "Running" label alongside LED)
- Screen reader accessible labels for cards, buttons, and log output

## 7. Coding Standards & Security (Vader Shield)
- **Vader Shield:** STRICT contextBridge isolation. `nodeIntegration: false`. No direct Node access in renderer. All privileged operations exposed only through secure preload scripts.
- **Naming Conventions:**
  - Functions/Classes: Prefix with `msc_` where applicable
  - CSS/Tailwind: Prefix custom classes with `msc-` to avoid framework conflicts
- **Repair Suite:** All AST transformations must utilize `vader-fix-suspense.mjs` logic and generate `.vader-backup` files before modification
- **File I/O:** Use Node `path` module for all cross-platform path handling; batch I/O to mitigate antivirus overhead

## 8. Implementation Requirements
- **Process Restoration:** On initialization, call `pm2.list()` to sync UI state with active projects
- **Port Management:** Implement auto-increment logic (up to 10 attempts) for occupied ports; if exhausted, show toast notification
- **Footer Net / Purge:** **Net** LED + **Purge env** reflect **3000** / **3001** / **9222** (green = **`forgeReady`** all idle; amber = **node/electron** only, incl. CDP; red = foreign); bounded (~**500ms**) port-health probe after purge; **`vpe:purge-launcher-ports`** uses **`taskkill /F /PID`** only (no **`/T`**) and skips **`process.pid`** / **`process.ppid`**
- **Nuke Action:** Canonical environment reset is **`npm run vpe:nuke-install`** (see **`Project-Bible.md` §7**): attempts **`taskkill`** on **`node.exe`**, purges **`node_modules`**, **`.next`**, **`dist`**, **`package-lock.json`**, then **`npm install`**.
- **Signature:** Every footer must include "Powered by the MSC Media Engine" with the **current** release version string (match root **`package.json`** / preload **`vpeInfo.version`**).

## 9. Error Handling & Feedback States
- **Toasts:** Top-right corner, dark background with red left accent border, auto-dismiss after 4 seconds; used for start, stop, nuke, and port-lock failures
- **Card Alerts:** PM2 crash loops or exhausted port increments flagged directly on the project card (red border + warning icon + error snippet)
- **Global Error Boundary:** Top-level React boundary catches UI render failures and offers a recovery option
- **Empty State:** Centered icon and text "Add a project to get started" with a CTA button when no projects registered
- **Error State (Cards):** Red border, warning icon, error message snippet

## 10. Session & Data Discipline
- **Snapshots:** Update `Session-Snapshots.md` at meaningful handoff points.
- **Milestones:** Add rollback rows to `Restore-Points.md` for major architectural changes.
- **Media Safety:** Store generated assets under project-root `media/` only; no absolute machine-specific paths in code.

## 11. Data Schema (SQLite catalog; legacy `projects.json` shape)
Runtime persistence is **SQLite** (`projects` table and related columns). The JSON below is the **logical** shape agents use when reasoning about a row; **authoritative columns** match `persistent-store.js` / migrations.

### 🚀 VPE-JediBuild Deployment Protocol
- **Trigger Phrase**: "Upload Build"
- **Context**: When this phrase is used, the agent must execute the automated deployment script.
- **Commands to Run**: 
  1. Verify the `dist` folder exists and contains an `.exe`.
  2. Execute: `powershell.exe -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File "D:\Cursor_Projectz\Node-Launcher-v3\scripts\upload_build.ps1"`
- **Expected Outcome**: The script will zip the `win-unpacked` folder, auto-increment the patch counter on GitHub tags (e.g. `VPE-JediBuild-v1.3-v1.2` when your branch is `VPE-JediBuild-v1.3`, or `VPE-JediBuild-main-v1.2` on other branches), and push the release to GitHub.

**`path` (Sovereign):** The registry **`path`** is the **user repo root** string the UI and **`vpe:save-settings`** trust for persistence. **`msc_normalizePersistedProjectPath`** applies vault + `vpe-local-data` guards only — **no save-time gate** on folder existence or **`package.json`** (reclaimed / half-linked rows allowed). Stricter validation applies only for **spawn** / tooling paths.

**Vault thumbnails:** Internal card thumbnail filename is **strictly** **`_vpe_thumb.png`** inside each project’s vault folder under **`media/vault`** (never use ad hoc basenames for the canonical engine thumb).

```json
{
  "projects": [
    {
      "id": "uuid-v4",
      "path": "string",
      "displayName": "string",
      "portLock": "boolean",
      "preferredPort": "number",
      "detectedPackageManager": "npm|yarn|pnpm",
      "detectedStartScript": "string",
      "status": "running|stopped",
      "lastThumbnail": "string",
      "createdAt": "ISO8601",
      "lastLaunched": "ISO8601"
    }
  ]
}
```
